# Helios Flutter

Read **`AGENTS.md`** at the repo root for architecture, env vars, and plugin rules.

- **Plugins never own Google Sign-In**; only the host shows the **single Google login** screen.
- Identity tokens for APIs: **Helios JWT from Helios Core** after Google ID token exchange — not the Google access token.
- Feature packages depend on **`helios_auth_contract`** only; the host implements `HeliosAuth` and injects it into plugin UIs/routes.

## Tests and verification

- Add or extend **automated tests** whenever behavior is non-trivial or regressions would hurt (parsers, HTTP clients, auth contract models, URL helpers, routing guards, etc.). Prefer **fast unit tests** with mocks (`http` `MockClient`, fakes) over flaky device-only checks when possible.
- After **any** meaningful code change, run **`flutter test`** and **`flutter analyze`** from the repo root and fix failures before considering the work done.
